<worksheet >
    <title>EL-3 Modeling with Exponential Functions</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>Complete both parts to get M. Complete one part with progress on the other to get P.</p>
  </introduction>
  <page>
    <exercise workspace="2.5in">
      <introduction><p>A 300 mg sample of a radioactive substance decayed to 84% of its original mass after 7 hours.</p><p><em>Set up and solve each
          of the following.  Leave your answers as integers, simplified fractions or in terms of natural logarithms.</em></p></introduction>
      <task><statement><p>What is the half-life of the substance?</p></statement></task>
      <task><statement><p>Find the mass remaining after 21 hours.</p></statement></task>
    </exercise>
    
  </page>
</worksheet>